 their crucial role of creating the intellectual elites who are indispensable for the running of national affairs and, at the same time, prepare their best-educated citizens for competition in a global market? To what extent is English really pushing other languages out of the academic environment? Drawing on the experience of several medium-sized language communities, this volume provides the reader with some important insights into how language policies can be successfully implemented. The different sociolinguistic contexts under scrutiny offer an invaluable comparative standpoint to understand what position can – or could – be occupied by each language at the level of higher education.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEducation, HighervCross-cultural studies. 0aLanguage policyvCross-cultural studies. 0aMultilingualismvCross-cultural studies. 0aNative language and educationvCross-cultural studies. 0aSociolinguisticsvCross-cultural studies. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Sociolinguistics.2bisacsh1 aBeukes, Anne-Marie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBretxa, Vanessa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHaberland, Hartmut, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParera, Eva Pons, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPreisler, Bent, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRam, Drorit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSherman, Tamah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVila Moreno, F. Xavier, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVila, F. Xavier, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYlönen, Sabine, econtributor.4ctb4https: